I"À<p>Yes and no. In my opinion, designers should do whatever it takes to be able to collaborate well including to communicate their concepts and ideas. If visualizing ideas through boxes and arrows of flowchart diagrams is what it takes, then do it. If code is what it takes, then learn to code.</p>

<p>Designers (including me in the past) are often confusing <em>crafts</em> with <em>tools</em>. Our shortcoming is we focused too much on tools</p>
